<TEXT>
<P>
 Saturday, March 4, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Clinton Assails Gay Marriage Ban
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PALO ALTO, Calif. (AP ) -- President Clinton is urging voters in California
to reject a ban on gay marriages, saying it is unnecessary because no state
currently honors such unions. Addressing a Democratic fund-raiser in San
Francisco on Friday night, the president said Proposition 22, which would bar
California from recognizing same-sex marriages should they become legal in any
other state, would have ''no practical effect whatever'' except to divert
attention from other, more serious issues.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Investigators Find Racist Writings
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WILKINSBURG, Pa. (AP) -- Racist writings describing hatred toward whites,
Jews and Asians, were found in the apartment of a black man accused in a
shooting rampage that left three people dead in suburban Pittsburgh. Court
documents released Friday said police found one paper called ''The Satan List''
that contained the names of businesses referred to as ''targets.'' Meanwhile,
Ronald Taylor, 39, was arraigned Friday on a third count of criminal homicide
after a third victim died.
