<HEADLINE> Indian Communist Mukherjee Dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- Geeta Mukherjee, veteran leader of the
Communist Party of India, died early Saturday of a massive heart
attack, officials of her party said. She was 76.
</P>
<P>
   Her death came as she was preparing to leave for a party program
in the northern town of Aligarh, 75 miles southeast of the capital,
New Delhi, the Press Trust of India news agency said.
</P>
<P>
   Mukherjee was one of the founding members of the communist
movement in the state of West Bengal. She was the widow of
prominent communist party leader Bishwanath Mukherjee.
</P>
<P>
   She also was secretary of the party's national council and its
deputy leader in the Lok Sabha, India's lower house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
   Mukherjee was deeply involved with women's issues, spearheading
the communists' demand for setting aside a third of all seats in
parliament and state legislatures for women.
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman for the Communist Party of India said Mukherjee's
body would be flown to Calcutta, capital of West Bengal state, and
the funeral would be held Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
