<HEADLINE> Bronx Detectives Find More Victims  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- A homicide probe in the Bronx suddenly
multiplied for police as they worked to notify next of kin and
instead found four more victims.
</P>
<P>
   In all, five people were found in three locations on Thursday
and Friday. Four were members of an extended Puerto Rican family,
neighbors said.
</P>
<P>
   The investigation broadened after police found Evelyn Santos,
39, shot and stabbed in an elevator at an apartment complex late
Thursday, said Det. Joseph Pentangelo, a police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Early Friday, detectives found Santos' 30-year-old sister,
Denise Santos, dead from stab wounds after coming to her nearby
home to speak with her about the slaying, said Howard Safir, the
city's police commissioner.
</P>
<P>
   Police say investigators then returned to the apartment complex
about 10 blocks away and found the bodies of the womens' brother,
34-year-old Edurado Santos, along with the fiance of Denise Santos
and a 14-year-old nephew to the women.
</P>
<P>
   Santos and his sister's fiance, 33-year-old Irvine Aguilar, had
been stabbed and shot to death, police said. The nephew,
14-year-old Ishamel Santos, was stabbed.
</P>
<P>
   Times of death had not been determined, Safir said. It was
unclear whether the slayings were the work of one person or more.
</P>
<P>
   Safir said there are ''some leads'' in the slayings, but he
named no suspects. There were no signs of forced entry at any of
the crime scenes, he added.
</P>
<P>
   A $10,000 police reward has been offered.
</P>
</TEXT>
