<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spice Upstaged by Former Member  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- The Spice Girls said something nice about
ex-member Geri Halliwell at the annual Brit awards, only to be
upstaged by the former Ginger Spice's raunchy musical act.
</P>
<P>
   Accepting the Outstanding Contribution to British Music award
for the Spice Girls' worldwide sales of 35 million albums Friday,
''Scary Spice'' Mel G said: ''We've all got to say a big, big thank
you to Geri because without her we wouldn't be able to do this.''
</P>
<P>
   Halliwell left the Spice Girls in May 1998, and her relations
with the four remaining members have been frosty.
</P>
<P>
   She emerged on stage from between a huge pair of inflatable
women's legs, then cavorted suggestively with a troupe of male
dancers. Her routine also featured four plump women pushing
trolleys and shopping for men, an apparent dig at her former group.
</P>
