<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian Ship in Danger in North Sea  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) -- A Romanian freighter was listing
sharply and in danger of capsizing in stormy conditions Saturday
off the Dutch North Sea coast, the Royal Coast Guard said.
</P>
<P>
   A Belgian Air Force helicopter plucked 11 of the 17 crew members
off the 6,000-ton Lugoj, which was listing at 30 degrees about 30
miles west of the shore point of Hoek van Holland, said coast guard
spokesman Peter van Oorschot.
</P>
<P>
   A Dutch chopper was standing by on a nearby oil platform to
collect the remaining crew members if necessary, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Two tug boats managed to secure the distressed vessel and were
pulling it toward the shore in near gale-force winds and eight-foot
waves.
</P>
<P>
   The spokesman said an attempt to right to boat had been
abandoned because it was close to capsizing. He said the 700-foot
freighter, which was carrying metallic cinders, had ''problems with
the loading.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
