<HEADLINE> 'The Rock' To Testify in Kid's Death  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- The attorney for a 12-year-old boy
accused of killing a 6-year-old playmate by slamming her onto a
table and railing has subpoenaed a professional wrestler to testify
at the boy's trial.
</P>
<P>
   The boy's lawyer, Jim Lewis, filed a subpoena Friday for Dwayne
''The Rock'' Johnson of the World Wrestling Federation.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis wants Johnson to show jurors how pro wrestlers choreograph
