<HEADLINE> Portuguese Consul Missing in Brazil  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) -- A Portuguese consul in southern
Brazil has disappeared, and police said Saturday they found a
bloody trail leading through his house.
</P>
<P>
   A maid reported Miguel Jose Fawor missing after she found his
home empty and the door open when she reported for work Friday at
the house in Curitiba, 420 miles southwest of Rio de Janeiro,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators found a bloody trail leading from an upstairs room
to the garage, police chief Fauze Salmen said. Later, Fawor's
Mercedes was found abandoned in a nearby neighborhood, a bloody
towel and hood in the trunk, Salmen said.
</P>
<P>
   A witness told police two men left the car there around midnight
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Fawor was last seen at his house late Thursday night by a
security guard, Salmen said. An answering machine was missing from
the house, probably because there was information recorded there
that could have helped investigators, he added.
</P>
<P>
   Fawor lived alone and had been stationed in Curitiba for three
years.
</P>
</TEXT>
