<HEADLINE> SuperSonics 93, Hawks 81  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Gary Payton scored 28 points as the Seattle
SuperSonics beat the Atlanta Hawks 93-81 Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Vin Baker added 16 for the Sonics, who had lost three of their
last four.
</P>
<P>
   Alan Henderson, Jim Jackson and Bimbo Coles each scored 11 to
lead Atlanta, which has lost three of four and six of its last
nine.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta's Dikembe Mutombo, who had more fouls (five) than points
(three), matched his season low in scoring. Isaiah Rider took only
three shots and finished with two points.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle took control with 1:01 left in the second quarter. With
the Sonics leading 39-35, Seattle went on a 10-3 run. Payton hit a
12-foot jump shot, Rashard Lewis made a 3-pointer and Baker
converted a pair of free throws. Then, Payton threw a long pass to
Brent Barry, whose 3-pointer from the left corner gave Seattle a
49-38 lead at the buzzer.
</P>
<P>
   The Hawks, coming off an 83-70 victory over the New York Knicks
on Friday night, jumped out to their biggest lead at 21-14 when
Jackson hit a 3-pointer with 40 seconds remaining in the first
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Rider, who leads Atlanta with 21.2 points per game, reported
late for the second consecutive game. Chris Crawford again started
in Rider's place and was 1-for-6 for two points.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Making four of six free throws, Payton needs 11 to pass
Lenny Wilkens, a former Seattle star player and coach, for fourth
place in franchise history. ... Barry missed his first seven shots,
including a breakaway dunk attempt, but hit his next four to finish
with 10 points. ... Atlanta dropped to 4-25 when trailing after
three quarters.
</P>
