<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian Swimmer Hurt in Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEDICINE HAT, Alberta (AP) -- Canadian swimmer Tara Sloan was in
critical condition Saturday after a highway accident in which the
van she was driving rolled over several times.
</P>
<P>
   Sloan, 20, of Calgary, was heading east Friday afternoon on
Highway 1 east of Medicine Hat when the accident occurred. The RCMP
said road conditions were good at the time of the accident and that
Sloan was wearing a seat belt.
</P>
<P>
   Sloan was airlifted to a Calgary hospital where she was in a
coma with head and abdominal injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Sloan, who specializes in the 100- and 200-meter breaststroke,
is a five-time Canadian champion. In last summer's Pan-Am Games in
Winnipeg, Manitoba, she finished eighth in the 200. She holds the
Canadian record in the 100.
</P>
</TEXT>
