<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Honduran Soccer Fans Keep Cool  </HEADLINE>
By MARCOS ALEMAN, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN PEDRO SULA, Honduras (AP) -- Despite fears of border tensions
spilling over onto the soccer field, fans kept their cool Saturday
night as Honduras beat Nicaragua 3-0 in a World Cup qualifier amid
tight security.
</P>
<P>
   Police were out in force in this northern Honduran city due to a
renewed border dispute between the two Central American countries.
No problems were reported.
</P>
<P>
   At the stadium, about 500 police and soldiers provided security
and the city banned the sale of alcoholic beverages to prevent
potential problems.
</P>
<P>
   Honduran fans seemed to make an extra effort to put the visitors
at ease. The crowd of 20,000 people -- overwhelmingly Honduran --
cheered the Nicaraguan national anthem before the game and the
Nicaraguan team as it left the field. On Friday, about 100
schoolchildren greeted the Nicaraguans at their hotel, giving them
flowers.
</P>
<P>
   But the Honduran team showed no mercy on the field. It dominated
play, leaving Nicaragua with no serious scoring opportunities.
</P>
<P>
   A crisis developed between the two countries in November when
Honduras approved a treaty with Colombia that conflicted with
Nicaraguan claims to a large swath of the Caribbean that is claimed
by Honduras.
</P>
<P>
   Troop maneuvers -- and rumors of maneuvers -- near the borders
have kept tensions high. Last month, Nicaragua claimed that
Honduran patrol boats fired on Nicaraguan naval boats in another
disputed region, the Gulf of Fonseca in the Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
   Nicaraguan President Arnoldo Aleman last week called the game
''dangerous'' and expressed hope that it would not lead to a repeat
of the so-called ''soccer war'' of 1969 between El Salvador and
Honduras, which followed a World Cup qualifying game. Most
historians say the soccer match had nothing to do with that border
conflict, in which some 6,000 people died.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-04-00 2343 </TRAILER>
